        <p><a href="ch67s13.html#MonstersH-I136">Zelekhuts</a> are charged with hunting down those who would deny justice-especially those who flee to escape punishment. Expert trackers, they use a combination of natural skill and magic to find fugitives wherever they may hide.</p>
        <p>A <a href="ch67s13.html#MonstersH-I136">zelekhut</a> may initially appear rather non-threatening-but when it is about to enter combat, it can cause two spiked chains to spring forth from its forearms as a free action. In similar fashion, it can cause a pair of golden metallic wings to emerge from its back. Retracting the chains or the wings is also a free action.</p>
        <div class="sect4" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage">
            <div>
              <div>
                <h5 class="title"><a name="id1974357"/>Combat</h5>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersH-I137"/>
          <p>Once it has found its fugitive, a <a href="ch67s13.html#MonstersH-I136">zelekhut</a> uses its speed and its spell-like abilities to cover the most likely escape routes. Then it immobilizes any defenders while attempting to protect any innocent bystanders. Finally, it apprehends the fugitive with its spiked chains, tripping or disarming the foe as needed.</p>
          <p>A <a href="ch67s13.html#MonstersH-I136">zelekhut's</a> natural weapons, as well as any weapons it wields, are treated as lawful-aligned for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.</p>
